translated: Jerlov, Emil Jonathan, professor, senior physician, senior lecturer, Gothenburg, born on March 17, 1891 in Eslöv. Married in 1918 to Sonja Essi Elisabet Liljebäck. — Completion of studies: Lund University, Bachelor of Medicine in 1909, Master of Medicine in 1913, Licentiate of Medicine in 1917, and Doctor of Medicine in 1925, all at the Karolinska Institute. Employed as a physician at the Garrison Hospital in Stockholm from 1915 to 1916, acting assistant surgeon at the Crown Princess Lovisa's Care Institution in 1916, stationed as a physician at a military facility in Kalix and acting physician at the hospital there in 1917, assistant physician at the General Maternity Hospital in Stockholm in 1918, and junior physician there from 1918 to 1920, the same positions at the Karlstad Hospital Surgical Department from 1920 to 1921, assistant doctor and junior physician at the Sabbatsberg Hospital Gynecological Department from 1922 to 1926, senior physician at the Helsingborg Maternity Hospital from 1926 to 1935, acting teacher of midwifery at the South Maternity Hospital for a total of five months in 1927, 1928, and 1929, professor and senior lecturer at the Gothenburg School of Midwifery, and senior physician at the Women's Clinic of the Sahlgrenska University Hospital since 1936. Member of the Health and Welfare Board in Helsingborg from 1927 to 1932. Author of around 30 publications on obstetrics, gynecology, and surgical topics. Received the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO).
